    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Fender Extensions</title>
        <para>The fender extensions are part of the body splash protection system. The wheel well openings in the fender
            extensions have been designed to provide splash and spray protection. These protect the lower front of the
            bus and cowl from splash and road debris kicked up by the front tires, and it also keeps the entry door step
            cleaner (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f47006125">Figure 125</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Release hood latches on each side of the hood and tilt the hood assembly forward.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the fender extension mounting bolts and nuts on the fender extension assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f47006125">Figure 125, Item 3</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f47006125" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/G47006125.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 125. Fender Extension Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. FENDER EXTENSION</callout1>
                <callout1>2. COWL</callout1>
                <callout1>3. FENDER EXTENSION MOUNTING HOLES AND BOLTS</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the three mounting bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f47006126">Figure 126, Item 2</hotlnk>) on the rear surface of the fender extension.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the fender extension (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f47006126">Figure 126, Item 1</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Follow same procedure to remove opposite side fender extension.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f47006126" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/G47006126.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 126. Fender Extension Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. FENDER EXTENSION</callout1>
                <callout1>2. MOUNTING BOLT HOLES</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcsubproc>
